184 DominatorTree *DT) { ----

186 return false; 0
187 ----
188 // Can't merge if there are multiple predecessors, or no predecessors. ----
189 BasicBlock *PredBB = BB->getUniquePredecessor(); 0
190 if (!PredBB) return false; 0
191 ----
192 // Don't break self-loops. ----
193 if (PredBB == BB) return false; 0
194 ----
195 // Don't break unwinding instructions or terminators with other side-effects. ----
196 Instruction *PTI = PredBB->getTerminator(); 0
197 if (PTI->isExceptionalTerminator() || PTI->mayHaveSideEffects()) 0

199 ----

201 if (!PredecessorWithTwoSuccessors && PredBB->getUniqueSuccessor() != BB) 0
202 return false; 0
203 ----

205 // Update BI to branch to BB's only successor instead of BB. ----
206 BranchInst *PredBB_BI; ----
207 BasicBlock *NewSucc = nullptr; 0
208 unsigned FallThruPath; ----
209 if (PredecessorWithTwoSuccessors) { 0
210 if (!(PredBB_BI = dyn_cast(PTI))) 0
211 return false; 0
212 BranchInst *BB_JmpI = dyn_cast(BB->getTerminator()); 0
213 if (!BB_JmpI || !BB_JmpI->isUnconditional()) 0
214 return false; 0

216 FallThruPath = PredBB_BI->getSuccessor(0) == BB ? 0 : 1; 0
217 } ----
218 ----
219 // Can't merge if there is PHI loop. ----
220 for (PHINode &PN : BB->phis()) 0
221 if (llvm::is_contained(PN.incoming_values(), &PN)) 0

227 // Begin by getting rid of unneeded PHIs. ----
228 SmallVector, 4> IncomingValues; 0

240 DomTreeNode *BBNode = DT->getNode(BB); 0

244 C->setIDom(PredNode); 0
245 } ----
246 } ----
247 // DTU update: Collect all the edges that exit BB. ----
248 // These dominator edges will be redirected from Pred. ----
249 std::vector Updates; 0
250 if (DTU) { 0
251 assert(!DT && "cannot use both DT and DTU for updates"); 0
252 // To avoid processing the same predecessor more than once. ----
253 SmallPtrSet SeenSuccs; 0
254 SmallPtrSet SuccsOfPredBB(succ_begin(PredBB), ----
255 succ_end(PredBB)); 0
256 Updates.reserve(Updates.size() + 2 * succ_size(BB) + 1); 0
257 // Add insert edges first. Experimentally, for the particular case of two ----
258 // blocks that can be merged, with a single successor and single predecessor ----
259 // respectively, it is beneficial to have all insert updates first. Deleting ----
260 // edges first may lead to unreachable blocks, followed by inserting edges ----

262 // times. We add inserts before deletes here to reduce compile time. ----

264 // This successor of BB may already be a PredBB's successor. ----

267 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Insert, PredBB, SuccOfBB}); 0
268 SeenSuccs.clear(); 0

277 // If there's nothing to move, mark the starting instruction as the last ----
278 // instruction in the block. Terminator instruction is handled separately. ----
279 if (Start == STI) 0

281 ----
282 // Move all definitions in the successor to the predecessor... ----
283 PredBB->splice(PTI->getIterator(), BB, BB->begin(), STI->getIterator()); 0
284 ----

287 ----
288 // Make all PHI nodes that referred to BB now refer to Pred as their ----

291 ----

293 // Delete the unconditional branch from BB. ----
294 BB->back().eraseFromParent(); 0
295 ----

298 } else { ----
299 // Delete the unconditional branch from the predecessor. ----

301 ----

364 /// Remove redundant instructions within sequences of consecutive dbg.value ----
365 /// instructions. This is done using a backward scan to keep the last dbg.value ----
366 /// describing a specific variable/fragment. ----
367 /// ----
368 /// BackwardScan strategy: ----
369 /// ---------------------- ----
370 /// Given a sequence of consecutive DbgValueInst like this ----
371 /// ----
372 /// dbg.value ..., "x", FragmentX1 (*) ----
373 /// dbg.value ..., "y", FragmentY1 ----
374 /// dbg.value ..., "x", FragmentX2 ----
375 /// dbg.value ..., "x", FragmentX1 (**) ----
376 /// ----
377 /// then the instruction marked with (*) can be removed (it is guaranteed to be ----
378 /// obsoleted by the instruction marked with (**) as the latter instruction is ----
379 /// describing the same variable using the same fragment info). ----
380 /// ----
381 /// Possible improvements: ----
382 /// - Check fully overlapping fragments and not only identical fragments. ----
383 /// - Support dbg.declare. dbg.label, and possibly other meta instructions being ----
384 /// part of the sequence of consecutive instructions. ----
385 static bool removeRedundantDbgInstrsUsingBackwardScan(BasicBlock *BB) { 0
386 SmallVector ToBeRemoved; 0
387 SmallDenseSet VariableSet; 0
388 for (auto &I : reverse(*BB)) { 0
389 if (DbgValueInst *DVI = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
390 DebugVariable Key(DVI->getVariable(), 0
391 DVI->getExpression(), 0
392 DVI->getDebugLoc()->getInlinedAt()); 0
393 auto R = VariableSet.insert(Key); 0
394 // If the variable fragment hasn't been seen before then we don't want ----
395 // to remove this dbg intrinsic. ----
396 if (R.second) 0
397 continue; 0
398 ----
399 if (auto *DAI = dyn_cast(DVI)) { 0
400 // Don't delete dbg.assign intrinsics that are linked to instructions. ----
401 if (!at::getAssignmentInsts(DAI).empty()) 0
402 continue; 0
403 // Unlinked dbg.assign intrinsics can be treated like dbg.values. ----
404 } ----
405 ----
406 // If the same variable fragment is described more than once it is enough ----
407 // to keep the last one (i.e. the first found since we for reverse ----
408 // iteration). ----
409 ToBeRemoved.push_back(DVI); 0
410 continue; 0
411 } 0
412 // Sequence with consecutive dbg.value instrs ended. Clear the map to ----
413 // restart identifying redundant instructions if case we find another ----
414 // dbg.value sequence. ----
415 VariableSet.clear(); 0
416 } ----
417 ----
418 for (auto &Instr : ToBeRemoved) 0
419 Instr->eraseFromParent(); 0
420 ----
421 return !ToBeRemoved.empty(); 0
422 } 0
423 ----
424 /// Remove redundant dbg.value instructions using a forward scan. This can ----
425 /// remove a dbg.value instruction that is redundant due to indicating that a ----
426 /// variable has the same value as already being indicated by an earlier ----
427 /// dbg.value. ----
428 /// ----
429 /// ForwardScan strategy: ----
430 /// --------------------- ----
431 /// Given two identical dbg.value instructions, separated by a block of ----
432 /// instructions that isn't describing the same variable, like this ----
433 /// ----
434 /// dbg.value X1, "x", FragmentX1 (**) ----
435 /// ----
436 /// dbg.value X1, "x", FragmentX1 (*) ----
437 /// ----
438 /// then the instruction marked with (*) can be removed. Variable "x" is already ----
439 /// described as being mapped to the SSA value X1. ----
440 /// ----
441 /// Possible improvements: ----
442 /// - Keep track of non-overlapping fragments. ----
443 static bool removeRedundantDbgInstrsUsingForwardScan(BasicBlock *BB) { 0
444 SmallVector ToBeRemoved; 0
445 DenseMap, DIExpression *>> ----
446 VariableMap; 0
447 for (auto &I : *BB) { 0
448 if (DbgValueInst *DVI = dyn_cast(&I)) { 0
449 DebugVariable Key(DVI->getVariable(), std::nullopt, 0
450 DVI->getDebugLoc()->getInlinedAt()); 0
451 auto VMI = VariableMap.find(Key); 0
452 auto *DAI = dyn_cast(DVI); 0
453 // A dbg.assign with no linked instructions can be treated like a ----
454 // dbg.value (i.e. can be deleted). ----
455 bool IsDbgValueKind = (!DAI || at::getAssignmentInsts(DAI).empty()); 0
456 ----
457 // Update the map if we found a new value/expression describing the ----
458 // variable, or if the variable wasn't mapped already. ----
459 SmallVector Values(DVI->getValues()); 0
460 if (VMI == VariableMap.end() || VMI->second.first != Values || 0
461 VMI->second.second != DVI->getExpression()) { 0
462 // Use a sentinal value (nullptr) for the DIExpression when we see a ----
463 // linked dbg.assign so that the next debug intrinsic will never match ----
464 // it (i.e. always treat linked dbg.assigns as if they're unique). ----
465 if (IsDbgValueKind) 0
466 VariableMap[Key] = {Values, DVI->getExpression()}; 0
467 else ----
468 VariableMap[Key] = {Values, nullptr}; 0
469 continue; 0
470 } ----
471 ----
472 // Don't delete dbg.assign intrinsics that are linked to instructions. ----
473 if (!IsDbgValueKind) 0
474 continue; 0
475 ToBeRemoved.push_back(DVI); 0
476 } 0
477 } ----
478 ----
479 for (auto &Instr : ToBeRemoved) 0
480 Instr->eraseFromParent(); 0
481 ----
482 return !ToBeRemoved.empty(); 0
483 } 0
484 ----
485 /// Remove redundant undef dbg.assign intrinsic from an entry block using a ----
486 /// forward scan. ----
487 /// Strategy: ----
488 /// --------------------- ----
489 /// Scanning forward, delete dbg.assign intrinsics iff they are undef, not ----
490 /// linked to an intrinsic, and don't share an aggregate variable with a debug ----
491 /// intrinsic that didn't meet the criteria. In other words, undef dbg.assigns ----
492 /// that come before non-undef debug intrinsics for the variable are ----
493 /// deleted. Given: ----
494 /// ----
495 /// dbg.assign undef, "x", FragmentX1 (*) ----
496 /// ----
497 /// dbg.value %V, "x", FragmentX2 ----
498 /// ----
499 /// dbg.assign undef, "x", FragmentX1 ----
500 /// ----
501 /// then (only) the instruction marked with (*) can be removed. ----
502 /// Possible improvements: ----
503 /// - Keep track of non-overlapping fragments. ----
504 static bool remomveUndefDbgAssignsFromEntryBlock(BasicBlock *BB) { 0
505 assert(BB->isEntryBlock() && "expected entry block"); 0
506 SmallVector ToBeRemoved; 0
507 DenseSet SeenDefForAggregate; 0
508 // Returns the DebugVariable for DVI with no fragment info. ----
509 auto GetAggregateVariable = [](DbgValueInst *DVI) { 0
510 return DebugVariable(DVI->getVariable(), std::nullopt, 0
511 DVI->getDebugLoc()->getInlinedAt()); 0
512 }; ----
513 ----
514 // Remove undef dbg.assign intrinsics that are encountered before ----
515 // any non-undef intrinsics from the entry block. ----
516 for (auto &I : *BB) { 0
517 DbgValueInst *DVI = dyn_cast(&I); 0
518 if (!DVI) 0
519 continue; 0
520 auto *DAI = dyn_cast(DVI); 0
521 bool IsDbgValueKind = (!DAI || at::getAssignmentInsts(DAI).empty()); 0
522 DebugVariable Aggregate = GetAggregateVariable(DVI); 0
523 if (!SeenDefForAggregate.contains(Aggregate)) { 0
524 bool IsKill = DVI->isKillLocation() && IsDbgValueKind; 0
525 if (!IsKill) { 0
526 SeenDefForAggregate.insert(Aggregate); 0
527 } else if (DAI) { 0
528 ToBeRemoved.push_back(DAI); 0
529 } ----
530 } ----
531 } ----
532 ----
533 for (DbgAssignIntrinsic *DAI : ToBeRemoved) 0
534 DAI->eraseFromParent(); 0
535 ----
536 return !ToBeRemoved.empty(); 0
537 } 0
538 ----
539 bool llvm::RemoveRedundantDbgInstrs(BasicBlock *BB) { 0
540 bool MadeChanges = false; 0
541 // By using the "backward scan" strategy before the "forward scan" strategy we ----
542 // can remove both dbg.value (2) and (3) in a situation like this: ----
543 // ----
544 // (1) dbg.value V1, "x", DIExpression() ----
545 // ... ----
546 // (2) dbg.value V2, "x", DIExpression() ----
547 // (3) dbg.value V1, "x", DIExpression() ----
548 // ----
549 // The backward scan will remove (2), it is made obsolete by (3). After ----
550 // getting (2) out of the way, the foward scan will remove (3) since "x" ----
551 // already is described as having the value V1 at (1). ----
552 MadeChanges |= removeRedundantDbgInstrsUsingBackwardScan(BB); 0
553 if (BB->isEntryBlock() && 0
554 isAssignmentTrackingEnabled(*BB->getParent()->getParent())) 0
555 MadeChanges |= remomveUndefDbgAssignsFromEntryBlock(BB); 0
556 MadeChanges |= removeRedundantDbgInstrsUsingForwardScan(BB); 0
557 ----
558 if (MadeChanges) 0
559 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Removed redundant dbg instrs from: " 0
560 << BB->getName() << "\n"); ----
561 return MadeChanges; 0
562 } ----

564 void llvm::ReplaceInstWithValue(BasicBlock::iterator &BI, Value *V) { 0
565 Instruction &I = *BI; 0
566 // Replaces all of the uses of the instruction with uses of the value ----
567 I.replaceAllUsesWith(V); 0
568 ----
569 // Make sure to propagate a name if there is one already. ----
570 if (I.hasName() && !V->hasName()) 0
571 V->takeName(&I); 0
572 ----
573 // Delete the unnecessary instruction now... ----
574 BI = BI->eraseFromParent(); 0
575 } 0
576 ----
577 void llvm::ReplaceInstWithInst(BasicBlock *BB, BasicBlock::iterator &BI, 0
578 Instruction *I) { ----
579 assert(I->getParent() == nullptr && 0
580 "ReplaceInstWithInst: Instruction already inserted into basic block!"); ----
581 ----
582 // Copy debug location to newly added instruction, if it wasn't already set ----
583 // by the caller. ----
584 if (!I->getDebugLoc()) 0
585 I->setDebugLoc(BI->getDebugLoc()); 0
586 ----
587 // Insert the new instruction into the basic block... ----
588 BasicBlock::iterator New = I->insertInto(BB, BI); 0
589 ----
590 // Replace all uses of the old instruction, and delete it. ----
591 ReplaceInstWithValue(BI, I); 0
592 ----
593 // Move BI back to point to the newly inserted instruction ----
594 BI = New; 0
595 } 0
596 ----
597 bool llvm::IsBlockFollowedByDeoptOrUnreachable(const BasicBlock *BB) { 0
598 // Remember visited blocks to avoid infinite loop ----
599 SmallPtrSet VisitedBlocks; 0
600 unsigned Depth = 0; 0
601 while (BB && Depth++ < MaxDeoptOrUnreachableSuccessorCheckDepth && 0
602 VisitedBlocks.insert(BB).second) { 0
603 if (isa(BB->getTerminator()) || 0
604 BB->getTerminatingDeoptimizeCall()) 0
605 return true; 0
606 BB = BB->getUniqueSuccessor(); 0
607 } ----
608 return false; 0
609 } 0
610 ----
611 void llvm::ReplaceInstWithInst(Instruction *From, Instruction *To) { 0
612 BasicBlock::iterator BI(From); 0
613 ReplaceInstWithInst(From->getParent(), BI, To); 0
614 } 0
615 ----
616 BasicBlock *llvm::SplitEdge(BasicBlock *BB, BasicBlock *Succ, DominatorTree *DT, 0
617 LoopInfo *LI, MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU, ----
618 const Twine &BBName) { ----
619 unsigned SuccNum = GetSuccessorNumber(BB, Succ); 0
620 ----
621 Instruction *LatchTerm = BB->getTerminator(); 0
622 ----
623 CriticalEdgeSplittingOptions Options = ----
624 CriticalEdgeSplittingOptions(DT, LI, MSSAU).setPreserveLCSSA(); 0
625 ----
626 if ((isCriticalEdge(LatchTerm, SuccNum, Options.MergeIdenticalEdges))) { 0
627 // If it is a critical edge, and the succesor is an exception block, handle ----
628 // the split edge logic in this specific function ----
629 if (Succ->isEHPad()) 0
630 return ehAwareSplitEdge(BB, Succ, nullptr, nullptr, Options, BBName); 0
631 ----
632 // If this is a critical edge, let SplitKnownCriticalEdge do it. ----
633 return SplitKnownCriticalEdge(LatchTerm, SuccNum, Options, BBName); 0
634 } ----
635 ----
636 // If the edge isn't critical, then BB has a single successor or Succ has a ----
637 // single pred. Split the block. ----
638 if (BasicBlock *SP = Succ->getSinglePredecessor()) { 0
639 // If the successor only has a single pred, split the top of the successor ----
640 // block. ----
641 assert(SP == BB && "CFG broken"); 0
642 SP = nullptr; 0
643 return SplitBlock(Succ, &Succ->front(), DT, LI, MSSAU, BBName, 0
644 /*Before=*/true); 0
645 } ----
646 ----
647 // Otherwise, if BB has a single successor, split it at the bottom of the ----
648 // block. ----
649 assert(BB->getTerminator()->getNumSuccessors() == 1 && 0
650 "Should have a single succ!"); ----
651 return SplitBlock(BB, BB->getTerminator(), DT, LI, MSSAU, BBName); 0
652 } ----
653 ----
654 void llvm::setUnwindEdgeTo(Instruction *TI, BasicBlock *Succ) { 0
655 if (auto *II = dyn_cast(TI)) 0
656 II->setUnwindDest(Succ); 0
657 else if (auto *CS = dyn_cast(TI)) 0
658 CS->setUnwindDest(Succ); 0
659 else if (auto *CR = dyn_cast(TI)) 0
660 CR->setUnwindDest(Succ); 0
661 else ----
662 llvm_unreachable("unexpected terminator instruction"); 0
663 } 0
664 ----
665 void llvm::updatePhiNodes(BasicBlock *DestBB, BasicBlock *OldPred, 0
666 BasicBlock *NewPred, PHINode *Until) { ----
667 int BBIdx = 0; 0
668 for (PHINode &PN : DestBB->phis()) { 0
669 // We manually update the LandingPadReplacement PHINode and it is the last ----
670 // PHI Node. So, if we find it, we are done. ----
671 if (Until == &PN) 0
672 break; 0
673 ----
674 // Reuse the previous value of BBIdx if it lines up. In cases where we ----
675 // have multiple phi nodes with *lots* of predecessors, this is a speed ----
676 // win because we don't have to scan the PHI looking for TIBB. This ----
677 // happens because the BB list of PHI nodes are usually in the same ----
678 // order. ----
679 if (PN.getIncomingBlock(BBIdx) != OldPred) 0
680 BBIdx = PN.getBasicBlockIndex(OldPred); 0
681 ----
682 assert(BBIdx != -1 && "Invalid PHI Index!"); 0
683 PN.setIncomingBlock(BBIdx, NewPred); 0
684 } ----
685 } 0
686 ----
687 BasicBlock *llvm::ehAwareSplitEdge(BasicBlock *BB, BasicBlock *Succ, 0
688 LandingPadInst *OriginalPad, ----
689 PHINode *LandingPadReplacement, ----
690 const CriticalEdgeSplittingOptions &Options, ----
691 const Twine &BBName) { ----
692 ----
693 auto *PadInst = Succ->getFirstNonPHI(); 0
694 if (!LandingPadReplacement && !PadInst->isEHPad()) 0
695 return SplitEdge(BB, Succ, Options.DT, Options.LI, Options.MSSAU, BBName); 0
696 ----
697 auto *LI = Options.LI; 0
698 SmallVector LoopPreds; 0
699 // Check if extra modifications will be required to preserve loop-simplify ----
700 // form after splitting. If it would require splitting blocks with IndirectBr ----
701 // terminators, bail out if preserving loop-simplify form is requested. ----
702 if (Options.PreserveLoopSimplify && LI) { 0
703 if (Loop *BBLoop = LI->getLoopFor(BB)) { 0
704 ----
705 // The only way that we can break LoopSimplify form by splitting a ----
706 // critical edge is when there exists some edge from BBLoop to Succ *and* ----
707 // the only edge into Succ from outside of BBLoop is that of NewBB after ----
708 // the split. If the first isn't true, then LoopSimplify still holds, ----
709 // NewBB is the new exit block and it has no non-loop predecessors. If the ----
710 // second isn't true, then Succ was not in LoopSimplify form prior to ----
711 // the split as it had a non-loop predecessor. In both of these cases, ----
712 // the predecessor must be directly in BBLoop, not in a subloop, or again ----
713 // LoopSimplify doesn't hold. ----
714 for (BasicBlock *P : predecessors(Succ)) { 0
715 if (P == BB) 0
716 continue; // The new block is known. 0
717 if (LI->getLoopFor(P) != BBLoop) { 0
718 // Loop is not in LoopSimplify form, no need to re simplify after ----
719 // splitting edge. ----
720 LoopPreds.clear(); 0
721 break; 0
722 } ----
723 LoopPreds.push_back(P); 0
724 } ----
725 // Loop-simplify form can be preserved, if we can split all in-loop ----
726 // predecessors. ----
727 if (any_of(LoopPreds, [](BasicBlock *Pred) { 0
728 return isa(Pred->getTerminator()); 0
729 })) { ----
730 return nullptr; 0
731 } ----
732 } ----
733 } ----
734 ----
735 auto *NewBB = ----
736 BasicBlock::Create(BB->getContext(), BBName, BB->getParent(), Succ); 0
737 setUnwindEdgeTo(BB->getTerminator(), NewBB); 0
738 updatePhiNodes(Succ, BB, NewBB, LandingPadReplacement); 0
739 ----
740 if (LandingPadReplacement) { 0
741 auto *NewLP = OriginalPad->clone(); 0
742 auto *Terminator = BranchInst::Create(Succ, NewBB); 0
743 NewLP->insertBefore(Terminator); 0
744 LandingPadReplacement->addIncoming(NewLP, NewBB); 0
745 } else { ----
746 Value *ParentPad = nullptr; 0
747 if (auto *FuncletPad = dyn_cast(PadInst)) 0
748 ParentPad = FuncletPad->getParentPad(); 0
749 else if (auto *CatchSwitch = dyn_cast(PadInst)) 0
750 ParentPad = CatchSwitch->getParentPad(); 0
751 else if (auto *CleanupPad = dyn_cast(PadInst)) 0
752 ParentPad = CleanupPad->getParentPad(); 0
753 else if (auto *LandingPad = dyn_cast(PadInst)) 0
754 ParentPad = LandingPad->getParent(); 0
755 else ----
756 llvm_unreachable("handling for other EHPads not implemented yet"); 0
757 ----
758 auto *NewCleanupPad = CleanupPadInst::Create(ParentPad, {}, BBName, NewBB); 0
759 CleanupReturnInst::Create(NewCleanupPad, Succ, NewBB); 0
760 } ----
761 ----
762 auto *DT = Options.DT; 0
763 auto *MSSAU = Options.MSSAU; 0
764 if (!DT && !LI) 0
765 return NewBB; 0
766 ----
767 if (DT) { 0
768 DomTreeUpdater DTU(DT, DomTreeUpdater::UpdateStrategy::Lazy); 0
769 SmallVector Updates; 0
770 ----
771 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Insert, BB, NewBB}); 0
772 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Insert, NewBB, Succ}); 0
773 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Delete, BB, Succ}); 0
774 ----
775 DTU.applyUpdates(Updates); 0
776 DTU.flush(); 0
777 ----
778 if (MSSAU) { 0
779 MSSAU->applyUpdates(Updates, *DT); 0
780 if (VerifyMemorySSA) 0
781 MSSAU->getMemorySSA()->verifyMemorySSA(); 0
782 } ----
783 } 0
784 ----
785 if (LI) { 0
786 if (Loop *BBLoop = LI->getLoopFor(BB)) { 0
787 // If one or the other blocks were not in a loop, the new block is not ----
788 // either, and thus LI doesn't need to be updated. ----
789 if (Loop *SuccLoop = LI->getLoopFor(Succ)) { 0
790 if (BBLoop == SuccLoop) { 0
791 // Both in the same loop, the NewBB joins loop. ----
792 SuccLoop->addBasicBlockToLoop(NewBB, *LI); 0
793 } else if (BBLoop->contains(SuccLoop)) { 0
794 // Edge from an outer loop to an inner loop. Add to the outer loop. ----
795 BBLoop->addBasicBlockToLoop(NewBB, *LI); 0
796 } else if (SuccLoop->contains(BBLoop)) { 0
797 // Edge from an inner loop to an outer loop. Add to the outer loop. ----
798 SuccLoop->addBasicBlockToLoop(NewBB, *LI); 0
799 } else { ----
800 // Edge from two loops with no containment relation. Because these ----
801 // are natural loops, we know that the destination block must be the ----
802 // header of its loop (adding a branch into a loop elsewhere would ----
803 // create an irreducible loop). ----
804 assert(SuccLoop->getHeader() == Succ && 0
805 "Should not create irreducible loops!"); ----
806 if (Loop *P = SuccLoop->getParentLoop()) 0
807 P->addBasicBlockToLoop(NewBB, *LI); 0
808 } ----
809 } ----
810 ----
811 // If BB is in a loop and Succ is outside of that loop, we may need to ----
812 // update LoopSimplify form and LCSSA form. ----
813 if (!BBLoop->contains(Succ)) { 0
814 assert(!BBLoop->contains(NewBB) && 0
815 "Split point for loop exit is contained in loop!"); ----
816 ----
817 // Update LCSSA form in the newly created exit block. ----
818 if (Options.PreserveLCSSA) { 0
819 createPHIsForSplitLoopExit(BB, NewBB, Succ); 0
820 } ----
821 ----
822 if (!LoopPreds.empty()) { 0
823 BasicBlock *NewExitBB = SplitBlockPredecessors( 0
824 Succ, LoopPreds, "split", DT, LI, MSSAU, Options.PreserveLCSSA); 0
825 if (Options.PreserveLCSSA) 0
826 createPHIsForSplitLoopExit(LoopPreds, NewExitBB, Succ); 0
827 } ----
828 } ----
829 } ----
830 } ----
831 ----
832 return NewBB; 0
833 } 0
834 ----
835 void llvm::createPHIsForSplitLoopExit(ArrayRef Preds, 0
836 BasicBlock *SplitBB, BasicBlock *DestBB) { ----
837 // SplitBB shouldn't have anything non-trivial in it yet. ----
838 assert((SplitBB->getFirstNonPHI() == SplitBB->getTerminator() || 0
839 SplitBB->isLandingPad()) && ----
840 "SplitBB has non-PHI nodes!"); ----
841 ----
842 // For each PHI in the destination block. ----
843 for (PHINode &PN : DestBB->phis()) { 0
844 int Idx = PN.getBasicBlockIndex(SplitBB); 0
845 assert(Idx >= 0 && "Invalid Block Index"); 0
846 Value *V = PN.getIncomingValue(Idx); 0
847 ----
848 // If the input is a PHI which already satisfies LCSSA, don't create ----
849 // a new one. ----
850 if (const PHINode *VP = dyn_cast(V)) 0
851 if (VP->getParent() == SplitBB) 0
852 continue; 0
853 ----
854 // Otherwise a new PHI is needed. Create one and populate it. ----
855 PHINode *NewPN = PHINode::Create( 0
856 PN.getType(), Preds.size(), "split", 0
857 SplitBB->isLandingPad() ? &SplitBB->front() : SplitBB->getTerminator()); 0
858 for (BasicBlock *BB : Preds) 0
859 NewPN->addIncoming(V, BB); 0
860 ----
861 // Update the original PHI. ----
862 PN.setIncomingValue(Idx, NewPN); 0
863 } ----
864 } 0
865 ----
866 unsigned ----
867 llvm::SplitAllCriticalEdges(Function &F, 0
868 const CriticalEdgeSplittingOptions &Options) { ----
869 unsigned NumBroken = 0; 0
870 for (BasicBlock &BB : F) { 0
871 Instruction *TI = BB.getTerminator(); 0
872 if (TI->getNumSuccessors() > 1 && !isa(TI)) 0
873 for (unsigned i = 0, e = TI->getNumSuccessors(); i != e; ++i) 0
874 if (SplitCriticalEdge(TI, i, Options)) 0
875 ++NumBroken; 0
876 } ----
877 return NumBroken; 0
878 } ----
879 ----
880 static BasicBlock *SplitBlockImpl(BasicBlock *Old, Instruction *SplitPt, 0
881 DomTreeUpdater *DTU, DominatorTree *DT, ----
882 LoopInfo *LI, MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU, ----
883 const Twine &BBName, bool Before) { ----
884 if (Before) { 0
885 DomTreeUpdater LocalDTU(DT, DomTreeUpdater::UpdateStrategy::Lazy); 0
886 return splitBlockBefore(Old, SplitPt, 0
887 DTU ? DTU : (DT ? &LocalDTU : nullptr), LI, MSSAU, 0
888 BBName); 0
889 } 0
890 BasicBlock::iterator SplitIt = SplitPt->getIterator(); 0
891 while (isa(SplitIt) || SplitIt->isEHPad()) { 0
892 ++SplitIt; 0
893 assert(SplitIt != SplitPt->getParent()->end()); 0
894 } ----
895 std::string Name = BBName.str(); 0
896 BasicBlock *New = Old->splitBasicBlock( 0
897 SplitIt, Name.empty() ? Old->getName() + ".split" : Name); 0
898 ----
899 // The new block lives in whichever loop the old one did. This preserves ----
900 // LCSSA as well, because we force the split point to be after any PHI nodes. ----
901 if (LI) 0
902 if (Loop *L = LI->getLoopFor(Old)) 0
903 L->addBasicBlockToLoop(New, *LI); 0
904 ----
905 if (DTU) { 0
906 SmallVector Updates; 0
907 // Old dominates New. New node dominates all other nodes dominated by Old. ----
908 SmallPtrSet UniqueSuccessorsOfOld; 0
909 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Insert, Old, New}); 0
910 Updates.reserve(Updates.size() + 2 * succ_size(New)); 0
911 for (BasicBlock *SuccessorOfOld : successors(New)) 0
912 if (UniqueSuccessorsOfOld.insert(SuccessorOfOld).second) { 0
913 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Insert, New, SuccessorOfOld}); 0
914 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Delete, Old, SuccessorOfOld}); 0
915 } ----
916 ----
917 DTU->applyUpdates(Updates); 0
918 } else if (DT) 0
919 // Old dominates New. New node dominates all other nodes dominated by Old. ----
920 if (DomTreeNode *OldNode = DT->getNode(Old)) { 0
921 std::vector Children(OldNode->begin(), OldNode->end()); 0
922 ----
923 DomTreeNode *NewNode = DT->addNewBlock(New, Old); 0
924 for (DomTreeNode *I : Children) 0
925 DT->changeImmediateDominator(I, NewNode); 0
926 } 0
927 ----
928 // Move MemoryAccesses still tracked in Old, but part of New now. ----
929 // Update accesses in successor blocks accordingly. ----
930 if (MSSAU) 0
931 MSSAU->moveAllAfterSpliceBlocks(Old, New, &*(New->begin())); 0
932 ----
933 return New; 0
934 } 0
935 ----
936 BasicBlock *llvm::SplitBlock(BasicBlock *Old, Instruction *SplitPt, 0
937 DominatorTree *DT, LoopInfo *LI, ----
938 MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU, const Twine &BBName, ----
939 bool Before) { ----
940 return SplitBlockImpl(Old, SplitPt, /*DTU=*/nullptr, DT, LI, MSSAU, BBName, 0
941 Before); 0
942 } ----
943 BasicBlock *llvm::SplitBlock(BasicBlock *Old, Instruction *SplitPt, 0
944 DomTreeUpdater *DTU, LoopInfo *LI, ----
945 MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU, const Twine &BBName, ----
946 bool Before) { ----
947 return SplitBlockImpl(Old, SplitPt, DTU, /*DT=*/nullptr, LI, MSSAU, BBName, 0
948 Before); 0
949 } ----
950 ----
951 BasicBlock *llvm::splitBlockBefore(BasicBlock *Old, Instruction *SplitPt, 0
952 DomTreeUpdater *DTU, LoopInfo *LI, ----
953 MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU, ----
954 const Twine &BBName) { ----
955 ----
956 BasicBlock::iterator SplitIt = SplitPt->getIterator(); 0
957 while (isa(SplitIt) || SplitIt->isEHPad()) 0
958 ++SplitIt; 0
959 std::string Name = BBName.str(); 0
960 BasicBlock *New = Old->splitBasicBlock( 0
961 SplitIt, Name.empty() ? Old->getName() + ".split" : Name, 0
962 /* Before=*/true); ----
963 ----
964 // The new block lives in whichever loop the old one did. This preserves ----
965 // LCSSA as well, because we force the split point to be after any PHI nodes. ----
966 if (LI) 0
967 if (Loop *L = LI->getLoopFor(Old)) 0
968 L->addBasicBlockToLoop(New, *LI); 0
969 ----
970 if (DTU) { 0
971 SmallVector DTUpdates; 0
972 // New dominates Old. The predecessor nodes of the Old node dominate ----
973 // New node. ----
974 SmallPtrSet UniquePredecessorsOfOld; 0
975 DTUpdates.push_back({DominatorTree::Insert, New, Old}); 0
976 DTUpdates.reserve(DTUpdates.size() + 2 * pred_size(New)); 0
977 for (BasicBlock *PredecessorOfOld : predecessors(New)) 0
978 if (UniquePredecessorsOfOld.insert(PredecessorOfOld).second) { 0
979 DTUpdates.push_back({DominatorTree::Insert, PredecessorOfOld, New}); 0
980 DTUpdates.push_back({DominatorTree::Delete, PredecessorOfOld, Old}); 0
981 } ----
982 ----
983 DTU->applyUpdates(DTUpdates); 0
984 ----
985 // Move MemoryAccesses still tracked in Old, but part of New now. ----
986 // Update accesses in successor blocks accordingly. ----
987 if (MSSAU) { 0
988 MSSAU->applyUpdates(DTUpdates, DTU->getDomTree()); 0
989 if (VerifyMemorySSA) 0
990 MSSAU->getMemorySSA()->verifyMemorySSA(); 0
991 } ----
992 } 0
993 return New; 0
994 } 0
995 ----
996 /// Update DominatorTree, LoopInfo, and LCCSA analysis information. ----
997 static void UpdateAnalysisInformation(BasicBlock *OldBB, BasicBlock *NewBB, 0
998 ArrayRef Preds, ----
999 DomTreeUpdater *DTU, DominatorTree *DT, ----
1000 LoopInfo *LI, MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU, ----
1001 bool PreserveLCSSA, bool &HasLoopExit) { ----
1002 // Update dominator tree if available. ----
1003 if (DTU) { 0
1004 // Recalculation of DomTree is needed when updating a forward DomTree and ----
1005 // the Entry BB is replaced. ----
1006 if (NewBB->isEntryBlock() && DTU->hasDomTree()) { 0
1007 // The entry block was removed and there is no external interface for ----
1008 // the dominator tree to be notified of this change. In this corner-case ----
1009 // we recalculate the entire tree. ----
1010 DTU->recalculate(*NewBB->getParent()); 0
1011 } else { ----
1012 // Split block expects NewBB to have a non-empty set of predecessors. ----
1013 SmallVector Updates; 0
1014 SmallPtrSet UniquePreds; 0
1015 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Insert, NewBB, OldBB}); 0
1016 Updates.reserve(Updates.size() + 2 * Preds.size()); 0
1017 for (auto *Pred : Preds) 0
1018 if (UniquePreds.insert(Pred).second) { 0
1019 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Insert, Pred, NewBB}); 0
1020 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Delete, Pred, OldBB}); 0
1021 } ----
1022 DTU->applyUpdates(Updates); 0
1023 } 0
1024 } else if (DT) { 0
1025 if (OldBB == DT->getRootNode()->getBlock()) { 0
1026 assert(NewBB->isEntryBlock()); 0
1027 DT->setNewRoot(NewBB); 0
1028 } else { ----
1029 // Split block expects NewBB to have a non-empty set of predecessors. ----
1030 DT->splitBlock(NewBB); 0
1031 } ----
1032 } ----
1033 ----
1034 // Update MemoryPhis after split if MemorySSA is available ----
1035 if (MSSAU) 0
1036 MSSAU->wireOldPredecessorsToNewImmediatePredecessor(OldBB, NewBB, Preds); 0
1037 ----
1038 // The rest of the logic is only relevant for updating the loop structures. ----
1039 if (!LI) 0
1040 return; 0
1041 ----
1042 if (DTU && DTU->hasDomTree()) 0
1043 DT = &DTU->getDomTree(); 0
1044 assert(DT && "DT should be available to update LoopInfo!"); 0
1045 Loop *L = LI->getLoopFor(OldBB); 0
1046 ----
1047 // If we need to preserve loop analyses, collect some information about how ----
1048 // this split will affect loops. ----
1049 bool IsLoopEntry = !!L; 0
1050 bool SplitMakesNewLoopHeader = false; 0
1051 for (BasicBlock *Pred : Preds) { 0
1052 // Preds that are not reachable from entry should not be used to identify if ----
1053 // OldBB is a loop entry or if SplitMakesNewLoopHeader. Unreachable blocks ----
1054 // are not within any loops, so we incorrectly mark SplitMakesNewLoopHeader ----
1055 // as true and make the NewBB the header of some loop. This breaks LI. ----
1056 if (!DT->isReachableFromEntry(Pred)) 0
1057 continue; 0
1058 // If we need to preserve LCSSA, determine if any of the preds is a loop ----
1059 // exit. ----
1060 if (PreserveLCSSA) 0
1061 if (Loop *PL = LI->getLoopFor(Pred)) 0
1062 if (!PL->contains(OldBB)) 0
1063 HasLoopExit = true; 0
1064 ----
1065 // If we need to preserve LoopInfo, note whether any of the preds crosses ----
1066 // an interesting loop boundary. ----
1067 if (!L) 0
1068 continue; 0
1069 if (L->contains(Pred)) 0
1070 IsLoopEntry = false; 0
1071 else ----
1072 SplitMakesNewLoopHeader = true; 0
1073 } ----
1074 ----
1075 // Unless we have a loop for OldBB, nothing else to do here. ----
1076 if (!L) 0
1077 return; 0
1078 ----
1079 if (IsLoopEntry) { 0
1080 // Add the new block to the nearest enclosing loop (and not an adjacent ----
1081 // loop). To find this, examine each of the predecessors and determine which ----
1082 // loops enclose them, and select the most-nested loop which contains the ----
1083 // loop containing the block being split. ----
1084 Loop *InnermostPredLoop = nullptr; 0
1085 for (BasicBlock *Pred : Preds) { 0
1086 if (Loop *PredLoop = LI->getLoopFor(Pred)) { 0
1087 // Seek a loop which actually contains the block being split (to avoid ----
1088 // adjacent loops). ----
1089 while (PredLoop && !PredLoop->contains(OldBB)) 0
1090 PredLoop = PredLoop->getParentLoop(); 0
1091 ----
1092 // Select the most-nested of these loops which contains the block. ----
1093 if (PredLoop && PredLoop->contains(OldBB) && 0
1094 (!InnermostPredLoop || 0
1095 InnermostPredLoop->getLoopDepth() < PredLoop->getLoopDepth())) 0
1096 InnermostPredLoop = PredLoop; 0
1097 } ----
1098 } ----
1099 ----
1100 if (InnermostPredLoop) 0
1101 InnermostPredLoop->addBasicBlockToLoop(NewBB, *LI); 0
1102 } else { ----
1103 L->addBasicBlockToLoop(NewBB, *LI); 0
1104 if (SplitMakesNewLoopHeader) 0
1105 L->moveToHeader(NewBB); 0
1106 } ----
1107 } ----
1108 ----
1109 /// Update the PHI nodes in OrigBB to include the values coming from NewBB. ----
1110 /// This also updates AliasAnalysis, if available. ----
1111 static void UpdatePHINodes(BasicBlock *OrigBB, BasicBlock *NewBB, 0
1112 ArrayRef Preds, BranchInst *BI, ----
1113 bool HasLoopExit) { ----
1114 // Otherwise, create a new PHI node in NewBB for each PHI node in OrigBB. ----
1115 SmallPtrSet PredSet(Preds.begin(), Preds.end()); 0
1116 for (BasicBlock::iterator I = OrigBB->begin(); isa(I); ) { 0
1117 PHINode *PN = cast(I++); 0
1118 ----
1119 // Check to see if all of the values coming in are the same. If so, we ----
1120 // don't need to create a new PHI node, unless it's needed for LCSSA. ----
1121 Value *InVal = nullptr; 0
1122 if (!HasLoopExit) { 0
1123 InVal = PN->getIncomingValueForBlock(Preds[0]); 0
1124 for (unsigned i = 0, e = PN->getNumIncomingValues(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1125 if (!PredSet.count(PN->getIncomingBlock(i))) 0
1126 continue; 0
1127 if (!InVal) 0
1128 InVal = PN->getIncomingValue(i); 0
1129 else if (InVal != PN->getIncomingValue(i)) { 0
1130 InVal = nullptr; 0
1131 break; 0
1132 } ----
1133 } ----
1134 } ----
1135 ----
1136 if (InVal) { 0
1137 // If all incoming values for the new PHI would be the same, just don't ----
1138 // make a new PHI. Instead, just remove the incoming values from the old ----
1139 // PHI. ----
1140 ----
1141 // NOTE! This loop walks backwards for a reason! First off, this minimizes ----
1142 // the cost of removal if we end up removing a large number of values, and ----
1143 // second off, this ensures that the indices for the incoming values ----
1144 // aren't invalidated when we remove one. ----
1145 for (int64_t i = PN->getNumIncomingValues() - 1; i >= 0; --i) 0
1146 if (PredSet.count(PN->getIncomingBlock(i))) 0
1147 PN->removeIncomingValue(i, false); 0
1148 ----
1149 // Add an incoming value to the PHI node in the loop for the preheader ----
1150 // edge. ----
1151 PN->addIncoming(InVal, NewBB); 0
1152 continue; 0
1153 } 0
1154 ----
1155 // If the values coming into the block are not the same, we need a new ----
1156 // PHI. ----
1157 // Create the new PHI node, insert it into NewBB at the end of the block ----
1158 PHINode *NewPHI = ----
1159 PHINode::Create(PN->getType(), Preds.size(), PN->getName() + ".ph", BI); 0
1160 ----
1161 // NOTE! This loop walks backwards for a reason! First off, this minimizes ----
1162 // the cost of removal if we end up removing a large number of values, and ----
1163 // second off, this ensures that the indices for the incoming values aren't ----
1164 // invalidated when we remove one. ----
1165 for (int64_t i = PN->getNumIncomingValues() - 1; i >= 0; --i) { 0
1166 BasicBlock *IncomingBB = PN->getIncomingBlock(i); 0
1167 if (PredSet.count(IncomingBB)) { 0
1168 Value *V = PN->removeIncomingValue(i, false); 0
1169 NewPHI->addIncoming(V, IncomingBB); 0
1170 } ----
1171 } ----
1172 ----
1173 PN->addIncoming(NewPHI, NewBB); 0
1174 } ----
1175 } 0
1176 ----
1177 static void SplitLandingPadPredecessorsImpl( ----
1178 BasicBlock *OrigBB, ArrayRef Preds, const char *Suffix1, ----
1179 const char *Suffix2, SmallVectorImpl &NewBBs, ----
1180 DomTreeUpdater *DTU, DominatorTree *DT, LoopInfo *LI, ----
1181 MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU, bool PreserveLCSSA); ----
1182 ----
1183 static BasicBlock * ----
1184 SplitBlockPredecessorsImpl(BasicBlock *BB, ArrayRef Preds, 0
1185 const char *Suffix, DomTreeUpdater *DTU, ----
1186 DominatorTree *DT, LoopInfo *LI, ----
1187 MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU, bool PreserveLCSSA) { ----
1188 // Do not attempt to split that which cannot be split. ----
1189 if (!BB->canSplitPredecessors()) 0
1190 return nullptr; 0
1191 ----
1192 // For the landingpads we need to act a bit differently. ----
1193 // Delegate this work to the SplitLandingPadPredecessors. ----
1194 if (BB->isLandingPad()) { 0
1195 SmallVector NewBBs; 0
1196 std::string NewName = std::string(Suffix) + ".split-lp"; 0
1197 ----
1198 SplitLandingPadPredecessorsImpl(BB, Preds, Suffix, NewName.c_str(), NewBBs, 0
1199 DTU, DT, LI, MSSAU, PreserveLCSSA); ----
1200 return NewBBs[0]; 0
1201 } 0
1202 ----
1203 // Create new basic block, insert right before the original block. ----
1204 BasicBlock *NewBB = BasicBlock::Create( 0
1205 BB->getContext(), BB->getName() + Suffix, BB->getParent(), BB); 0
1206 ----
1207 // The new block unconditionally branches to the old block. ----
1208 BranchInst *BI = BranchInst::Create(BB, NewBB); 0
1209 ----
1210 Loop *L = nullptr; 0
1211 BasicBlock *OldLatch = nullptr; 0
1212 // Splitting the predecessors of a loop header creates a preheader block. ----
1213 if (LI && LI->isLoopHeader(BB)) { 0
1214 L = LI->getLoopFor(BB); 0
1215 // Using the loop start line number prevents debuggers stepping into the ----
1216 // loop body for this instruction. ----
1217 BI->setDebugLoc(L->getStartLoc()); 0
1218 ----
1219 // If BB is the header of the Loop, it is possible that the loop is ----
1220 // modified, such that the current latch does not remain the latch of the ----
1221 // loop. If that is the case, the loop metadata from the current latch needs ----
1222 // to be applied to the new latch. ----
1223 OldLatch = L->getLoopLatch(); 0
1224 } else ----
1225 BI->setDebugLoc(BB->getFirstNonPHIOrDbg()->getDebugLoc()); 0
1226 ----
1227 // Move the edges from Preds to point to NewBB instead of BB. ----
1228 for (BasicBlock *Pred : Preds) { 0
1229 // This is slightly more strict than necessary; the minimum requirement ----
1230 // is that there be no more than one indirectbr branching to BB. And ----
1231 // all BlockAddress uses would need to be updated. ----
1232 assert(!isa(Pred->getTerminator()) && 0
1233 "Cannot split an edge from an IndirectBrInst"); ----
1234 Pred->getTerminator()->replaceSuccessorWith(BB, NewBB); 0
1235 } ----
1236 ----
1237 // Insert a new PHI node into NewBB for every PHI node in BB and that new PHI ----
1238 // node becomes an incoming value for BB's phi node. However, if the Preds ----
1239 // list is empty, we need to insert dummy entries into the PHI nodes in BB to ----
1240 // account for the newly created predecessor. ----
1241 if (Preds.empty()) { 0
1242 // Insert dummy values as the incoming value. ----
1243 for (BasicBlock::iterator I = BB->begin(); isa(I); ++I) 0
1244 cast(I)->addIncoming(PoisonValue::get(I->getType()), NewBB); 0
1245 } ----
1246 ----
1247 // Update DominatorTree, LoopInfo, and LCCSA analysis information. ----
1248 bool HasLoopExit = false; 0
1249 UpdateAnalysisInformation(BB, NewBB, Preds, DTU, DT, LI, MSSAU, PreserveLCSSA, 0
1250 HasLoopExit); ----
1251 ----
1252 if (!Preds.empty()) { 0
1253 // Update the PHI nodes in BB with the values coming from NewBB. ----
1254 UpdatePHINodes(BB, NewBB, Preds, BI, HasLoopExit); 0
1255 } ----
1256 ----
1257 if (OldLatch) { 0
1258 BasicBlock *NewLatch = L->getLoopLatch(); 0
1259 if (NewLatch != OldLatch) { 0
1260 MDNode *MD = OldLatch->getTerminator()->getMetadata("llvm.loop"); 0
1261 NewLatch->getTerminator()->setMetadata("llvm.loop", MD); 0
1262 // It's still possible that OldLatch is the latch of another inner loop, ----
1263 // in which case we do not remove the metadata. ----
1264 Loop *IL = LI->getLoopFor(OldLatch); 0
1265 if (IL && IL->getLoopLatch() != OldLatch) 0
1266 OldLatch->getTerminator()->setMetadata("llvm.loop", nullptr); 0
1267 } ----
1268 } ----
1269 ----
1270 return NewBB; 0
1271 } ----
1272 ----
1273 BasicBlock *llvm::SplitBlockPredecessors(BasicBlock *BB, 0
1274 ArrayRef Preds, ----
1275 const char *Suffix, DominatorTree *DT, ----
1276 LoopInfo *LI, MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU, ----
1277 bool PreserveLCSSA) { ----
1278 return SplitBlockPredecessorsImpl(BB, Preds, Suffix, /*DTU=*/nullptr, DT, LI, 0
1279 MSSAU, PreserveLCSSA); 0
1280 } ----
1281 BasicBlock *llvm::SplitBlockPredecessors(BasicBlock *BB, 0
1282 ArrayRef Preds, ----
1283 const char *Suffix, ----
1284 DomTreeUpdater *DTU, LoopInfo *LI, ----
1285 MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU, ----
1286 bool PreserveLCSSA) { ----
1287 return SplitBlockPredecessorsImpl(BB, Preds, Suffix, DTU, 0
1288 /*DT=*/nullptr, LI, MSSAU, PreserveLCSSA); 0
1289 } ----
1290 ----
1291 static void SplitLandingPadPredecessorsImpl( 0
1292 BasicBlock *OrigBB, ArrayRef Preds, const char *Suffix1, ----
1293 const char *Suffix2, SmallVectorImpl &NewBBs, ----
1294 DomTreeUpdater *DTU, DominatorTree *DT, LoopInfo *LI, ----
1295 MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU, bool PreserveLCSSA) { ----
1296 assert(OrigBB->isLandingPad() && "Trying to split a non-landing pad!"); 0
1297 ----
1298 // Create a new basic block for OrigBB's predecessors listed in Preds. Insert ----
1299 // it right before the original block. ----
1300 BasicBlock *NewBB1 = BasicBlock::Create(OrigBB->getContext(), 0
1301 OrigBB->getName() + Suffix1, 0
1302 OrigBB->getParent(), OrigBB); ----
1303 NewBBs.push_back(NewBB1); 0
1304 ----
1305 // The new block unconditionally branches to the old block. ----
1306 BranchInst *BI1 = BranchInst::Create(OrigBB, NewBB1); 0
1307 BI1->setDebugLoc(OrigBB->getFirstNonPHI()->getDebugLoc()); 0
1308 ----
1309 // Move the edges from Preds to point to NewBB1 instead of OrigBB. ----
1310 for (BasicBlock *Pred : Preds) { 0
1311 // This is slightly more strict than necessary; the minimum requirement ----
1312 // is that there be no more than one indirectbr branching to BB. And ----
1313 // all BlockAddress uses would need to be updated. ----
1314 assert(!isa(Pred->getTerminator()) && 0
1315 "Cannot split an edge from an IndirectBrInst"); ----
1316 Pred->getTerminator()->replaceUsesOfWith(OrigBB, NewBB1); 0
1317 } ----
1318 ----
1319 bool HasLoopExit = false; 0
1320 UpdateAnalysisInformation(OrigBB, NewBB1, Preds, DTU, DT, LI, MSSAU, 0
1321 PreserveLCSSA, HasLoopExit); ----
1322 ----
1323 // Update the PHI nodes in OrigBB with the values coming from NewBB1. ----
1324 UpdatePHINodes(OrigBB, NewBB1, Preds, BI1, HasLoopExit); 0
1325 ----
1326 // Move the remaining edges from OrigBB to point to NewBB2. ----
1327 SmallVector NewBB2Preds; 0
1328 for (pred_iterator i = pred_begin(OrigBB), e = pred_end(OrigBB); 0
1329 i != e; ) { 0
1330 BasicBlock *Pred = *i++; 0
1331 if (Pred == NewBB1) continue; 0
1332 assert(!isa(Pred->getTerminator()) && 0
1333 "Cannot split an edge from an IndirectBrInst"); ----
1334 NewBB2Preds.push_back(Pred); 0
1335 e = pred_end(OrigBB); 0
1336 } ----
1337 ----
1338 BasicBlock *NewBB2 = nullptr; 0
1339 if (!NewBB2Preds.empty()) { 0
1340 // Create another basic block for the rest of OrigBB's predecessors. ----
1341 NewBB2 = BasicBlock::Create(OrigBB->getContext(), 0
1342 OrigBB->getName() + Suffix2, 0
1343 OrigBB->getParent(), OrigBB); ----
1344 NewBBs.push_back(NewBB2); 0
1345 ----
1346 // The new block unconditionally branches to the old block. ----
1347 BranchInst *BI2 = BranchInst::Create(OrigBB, NewBB2); 0
1348 BI2->setDebugLoc(OrigBB->getFirstNonPHI()->getDebugLoc()); 0
1349 ----
1350 // Move the remaining edges from OrigBB to point to NewBB2. ----
1351 for (BasicBlock *NewBB2Pred : NewBB2Preds) 0
1352 NewBB2Pred->getTerminator()->replaceUsesOfWith(OrigBB, NewBB2); 0
1353 ----
1354 // Update DominatorTree, LoopInfo, and LCCSA analysis information. ----
1355 HasLoopExit = false; 0
1356 UpdateAnalysisInformation(OrigBB, NewBB2, NewBB2Preds, DTU, DT, LI, MSSAU, 0
1357 PreserveLCSSA, HasLoopExit); ----
1358 ----
1359 // Update the PHI nodes in OrigBB with the values coming from NewBB2. ----
1360 UpdatePHINodes(OrigBB, NewBB2, NewBB2Preds, BI2, HasLoopExit); 0
1361 } ----
1362 ----
1363 LandingPadInst *LPad = OrigBB->getLandingPadInst(); 0
1364 Instruction *Clone1 = LPad->clone(); 0
1365 Clone1->setName(Twine("lpad") + Suffix1); 0
1366 Clone1->insertInto(NewBB1, NewBB1->getFirstInsertionPt()); 0
1367 ----
1368 if (NewBB2) { 0
1369 Instruction *Clone2 = LPad->clone(); 0
1370 Clone2->setName(Twine("lpad") + Suffix2); 0
1371 Clone2->insertInto(NewBB2, NewBB2->getFirstInsertionPt()); 0
1372 ----
1373 // Create a PHI node for the two cloned landingpad instructions only ----
1374 // if the original landingpad instruction has some uses. ----
1375 if (!LPad->use_empty()) { 0
1376 assert(!LPad->getType()->isTokenTy() && 0
1377 "Split cannot be applied if LPad is token type. Otherwise an " ----
1378 "invalid PHINode of token type would be created."); ----
1379 PHINode *PN = PHINode::Create(LPad->getType(), 2, "lpad.phi", LPad); 0
1380 PN->addIncoming(Clone1, NewBB1); 0
1381 PN->addIncoming(Clone2, NewBB2); 0
1382 LPad->replaceAllUsesWith(PN); 0
1383 } ----
1384 LPad->eraseFromParent(); 0
1385 } else { ----
1386 // There is no second clone. Just replace the landing pad with the first ----
1387 // clone. ----
1388 LPad->replaceAllUsesWith(Clone1); 0
1389 LPad->eraseFromParent(); 0
1390 } ----
1391 } 0
1392 ----
1393 void llvm::SplitLandingPadPredecessors(BasicBlock *OrigBB, 0
1394 ArrayRef Preds, ----
1395 const char *Suffix1, const char *Suffix2, ----
1396 SmallVectorImpl &NewBBs, ----
1397 DominatorTree *DT, LoopInfo *LI, ----
1398 MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU, ----
1399 bool PreserveLCSSA) { ----
1400 return SplitLandingPadPredecessorsImpl( 0
1401 OrigBB, Preds, Suffix1, Suffix2, NewBBs, ----
1402 /*DTU=*/nullptr, DT, LI, MSSAU, PreserveLCSSA); 0
1403 } ----
1404 void llvm::SplitLandingPadPredecessors(BasicBlock *OrigBB, 0
1405 ArrayRef Preds, ----
1406 const char *Suffix1, const char *Suffix2, ----
1407 SmallVectorImpl &NewBBs, ----
1408 DomTreeUpdater *DTU, LoopInfo *LI, ----
1409 MemorySSAUpdater *MSSAU, ----
1410 bool PreserveLCSSA) { ----
1411 return SplitLandingPadPredecessorsImpl(OrigBB, Preds, Suffix1, Suffix2, 0
1412 NewBBs, DTU, /*DT=*/nullptr, LI, MSSAU, ----
1413 PreserveLCSSA); 0
1414 } ----
1415 ----
1416 ReturnInst *llvm::FoldReturnIntoUncondBranch(ReturnInst *RI, BasicBlock *BB, 0
1417 BasicBlock *Pred, ----
1418 DomTreeUpdater *DTU) { ----
1419 Instruction *UncondBranch = Pred->getTerminator(); 0
1420 // Clone the return and add it to the end of the predecessor. ----
1421 Instruction *NewRet = RI->clone(); 0
1422 NewRet->insertInto(Pred, Pred->end()); 0
1423 ----
1424 // If the return instruction returns a value, and if the value was a ----
1425 // PHI node in "BB", propagate the right value into the return. ----
1426 for (Use &Op : NewRet->operands()) { 0
1427 Value *V = Op; 0
1428 Instruction *NewBC = nullptr; 0
1429 if (BitCastInst *BCI = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
1430 // Return value might be bitcasted. Clone and insert it before the ----
1431 // return instruction. ----
1432 V = BCI->getOperand(0); 0
1433 NewBC = BCI->clone(); 0
1434 NewBC->insertInto(Pred, NewRet->getIterator()); 0
1435 Op = NewBC; 0
1436 } ----
1437 ----
1438 Instruction *NewEV = nullptr; 0
1439 if (ExtractValueInst *EVI = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
1440 V = EVI->getOperand(0); 0
1441 NewEV = EVI->clone(); 0
1442 if (NewBC) { 0
1443 NewBC->setOperand(0, NewEV); 0
1444 NewEV->insertInto(Pred, NewBC->getIterator()); 0
1445 } else { ----
1446 NewEV->insertInto(Pred, NewRet->getIterator()); 0
1447 Op = NewEV; 0
1448 } ----
1449 } ----
1450 ----
1451 if (PHINode *PN = dyn_cast(V)) { 0
1452 if (PN->getParent() == BB) { 0
1453 if (NewEV) { 0
1454 NewEV->setOperand(0, PN->getIncomingValueForBlock(Pred)); 0
1455 } else if (NewBC) 0
1456 NewBC->setOperand(0, PN->getIncomingValueForBlock(Pred)); 0
1457 else ----
1458 Op = PN->getIncomingValueForBlock(Pred); 0
1459 } ----
1460 } ----
1461 } ----
1462 ----
1463 // Update any PHI nodes in the returning block to realize that we no ----
1464 // longer branch to them. ----
1465 BB->removePredecessor(Pred); 0
1466 UncondBranch->eraseFromParent(); 0
1467 ----
1468 if (DTU) 0
1469 DTU->applyUpdates({{DominatorTree::Delete, Pred, BB}}); 0
1470 ----
1471 return cast(NewRet); 0
1472 } ----
1473 ----
1474 Instruction *llvm::SplitBlockAndInsertIfThen(Value *Cond, 0
1475 Instruction *SplitBefore, ----
1476 bool Unreachable, ----
1477 MDNode *BranchWeights, ----
1478 DomTreeUpdater *DTU, LoopInfo *LI, ----
1479 BasicBlock *ThenBlock) { ----
1480 SplitBlockAndInsertIfThenElse( 0
1481 Cond, SplitBefore, &ThenBlock, /* ElseBlock */ nullptr, ----
1482 /* UnreachableThen */ Unreachable, ----
1483 /* UnreachableElse */ false, BranchWeights, DTU, LI); ----
1484 return ThenBlock->getTerminator(); 0
1485 } ----
1486 ----

1489 bool Unreachable, ----
1490 MDNode *BranchWeights, ----

1492 BasicBlock *ElseBlock) { ----
1493 SplitBlockAndInsertIfThenElse( 0
1494 Cond, SplitBefore, /* ThenBlock */ nullptr, &ElseBlock, ----
1495 /* UnreachableThen */ false, ----
1496 /* UnreachableElse */ Unreachable, BranchWeights, DTU, LI); ----
1497 return ElseBlock->getTerminator(); 0
1498 } ----
1499 ----
1500 void llvm::SplitBlockAndInsertIfThenElse(Value *Cond, Instruction *SplitBefore, 0
1501 Instruction **ThenTerm, ----
1502 Instruction **ElseTerm, ----
1503 MDNode *BranchWeights, ----
1504 DomTreeUpdater *DTU, LoopInfo *LI) { ----
1505 BasicBlock *ThenBlock = nullptr; 0
1506 BasicBlock *ElseBlock = nullptr; 0
1507 SplitBlockAndInsertIfThenElse( 0
1508 Cond, SplitBefore, &ThenBlock, &ElseBlock, /* UnreachableThen */ false, ----
1509 /* UnreachableElse */ false, BranchWeights, DTU, LI); ----
1510 ----
1511 *ThenTerm = ThenBlock->getTerminator(); 0
1512 *ElseTerm = ElseBlock->getTerminator(); 0
1513 } 0
1514 ----
1515 void llvm::SplitBlockAndInsertIfThenElse( 0
1516 Value *Cond, Instruction *SplitBefore, BasicBlock **ThenBlock, ----
1517 BasicBlock **ElseBlock, bool UnreachableThen, bool UnreachableElse, ----
1518 MDNode *BranchWeights, DomTreeUpdater *DTU, LoopInfo *LI) { ----
1519 assert((ThenBlock || ElseBlock) && 0
1520 "At least one branch block must be created"); ----
1521 assert((!UnreachableThen || !UnreachableElse) && 0
1522 "Split block tail must be reachable"); ----
1523 ----
1524 SmallVector Updates; 0
1525 SmallPtrSet UniqueOrigSuccessors; 0
1526 BasicBlock *Head = SplitBefore->getParent(); 0
1527 if (DTU) { 0
1528 UniqueOrigSuccessors.insert(succ_begin(Head), succ_end(Head)); 0
1529 Updates.reserve(4 + 2 * UniqueOrigSuccessors.size()); 0
1530 } ----
1531 ----
1532 LLVMContext &C = Head->getContext(); 0
1533 BasicBlock *Tail = Head->splitBasicBlock(SplitBefore->getIterator()); 0
1534 BasicBlock *TrueBlock = Tail; 0
1535 BasicBlock *FalseBlock = Tail; 0
1536 bool ThenToTailEdge = false; 0
1537 bool ElseToTailEdge = false; 0
1538 ----
1539 // Encapsulate the logic around creation/insertion/etc of a new block. ----
1540 auto handleBlock = [&](BasicBlock **PBB, bool Unreachable, BasicBlock *&BB, 0
1541 bool &ToTailEdge) { ----
1542 if (PBB == nullptr) 0
1543 return; // Do not create/insert a block. 0
1544 ----
1545 if (*PBB) 0
1546 BB = *PBB; // Caller supplied block, use it. 0
1547 else { ----
1548 // Create a new block. ----
1549 BB = BasicBlock::Create(C, "", Head->getParent(), Tail); 0
1550 if (Unreachable) 0
1551 (void)new UnreachableInst(C, BB); 0
1552 else { ----
1553 (void)BranchInst::Create(Tail, BB); 0
1554 ToTailEdge = true; 0
1555 } ----
1556 BB->getTerminator()->setDebugLoc(SplitBefore->getDebugLoc()); 0
1557 // Pass the new block back to the caller. ----
1558 *PBB = BB; 0
1559 } ----
1560 }; 0
1561 ----
1562 handleBlock(ThenBlock, UnreachableThen, TrueBlock, ThenToTailEdge); 0
1563 handleBlock(ElseBlock, UnreachableElse, FalseBlock, ElseToTailEdge); 0
1564 ----
1565 Instruction *HeadOldTerm = Head->getTerminator(); 0
1566 BranchInst *HeadNewTerm = ----
1567 BranchInst::Create(/*ifTrue*/ TrueBlock, /*ifFalse*/ FalseBlock, Cond); 0
1568 HeadNewTerm->setMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_prof, BranchWeights); 0
1569 ReplaceInstWithInst(HeadOldTerm, HeadNewTerm); 0
1570 ----
1571 if (DTU) { 0
1572 Updates.emplace_back(DominatorTree::Insert, Head, TrueBlock); 0
1573 Updates.emplace_back(DominatorTree::Insert, Head, FalseBlock); 0
1574 if (ThenToTailEdge) 0
1575 Updates.emplace_back(DominatorTree::Insert, TrueBlock, Tail); 0
1576 if (ElseToTailEdge) 0
1577 Updates.emplace_back(DominatorTree::Insert, FalseBlock, Tail); 0
1578 for (BasicBlock *UniqueOrigSuccessor : UniqueOrigSuccessors) 0
1579 Updates.emplace_back(DominatorTree::Insert, Tail, UniqueOrigSuccessor); 0
1580 for (BasicBlock *UniqueOrigSuccessor : UniqueOrigSuccessors) 0
1581 Updates.emplace_back(DominatorTree::Delete, Head, UniqueOrigSuccessor); 0
1582 DTU->applyUpdates(Updates); 0
1583 } ----
1584 ----
1585 if (LI) { 0
1586 if (Loop *L = LI->getLoopFor(Head); L) { 0
1587 if (ThenToTailEdge) 0
1588 L->addBasicBlockToLoop(TrueBlock, *LI); 0
1589 if (ElseToTailEdge) 0
1590 L->addBasicBlockToLoop(FalseBlock, *LI); 0
1591 L->addBasicBlockToLoop(Tail, *LI); 0
1592 } ----
1593 } ----
1594 } 0
1595 ----
1596 std::pair ----
1597 llvm::SplitBlockAndInsertSimpleForLoop(Value *End, Instruction *SplitBefore) { 0
1598 BasicBlock *LoopPred = SplitBefore->getParent(); 0
1599 BasicBlock *LoopBody = SplitBlock(SplitBefore->getParent(), SplitBefore); 0
1600 BasicBlock *LoopExit = SplitBlock(SplitBefore->getParent(), SplitBefore); 0
1601 ----
1602 auto *Ty = End->getType(); 0
1603 auto &DL = SplitBefore->getModule()->getDataLayout(); 0
1604 const unsigned Bitwidth = DL.getTypeSizeInBits(Ty); 0
1605 ----
1606 IRBuilder<> Builder(LoopBody->getTerminator()); 0
1607 auto *IV = Builder.CreatePHI(Ty, 2, "iv"); 0
1608 auto *IVNext = ----
1609 Builder.CreateAdd(IV, ConstantInt::get(Ty, 1), IV->getName() + ".next", 0
1610 /*HasNUW=*/true, /*HasNSW=*/Bitwidth != 2); ----
1611 auto *IVCheck = Builder.CreateICmpEQ(IVNext, End, 0
1612 IV->getName() + ".check"); 0
1613 Builder.CreateCondBr(IVCheck, LoopExit, LoopBody); 0
1614 LoopBody->getTerminator()->eraseFromParent(); 0
1615 ----
1616 // Populate the IV PHI. ----
1617 IV->addIncoming(ConstantInt::get(Ty, 0), LoopPred); 0
1618 IV->addIncoming(IVNext, LoopBody); 0
1619 ----
1620 return std::make_pair(LoopBody->getFirstNonPHI(), IV); 0
1621 } 0
1622 ----
1623 void llvm::SplitBlockAndInsertForEachLane(ElementCount EC, 0
1624 Type *IndexTy, Instruction *InsertBefore, ----
1625 std::function Func) { ----
1626 ----
1627 IRBuilder<> IRB(InsertBefore); 0
1628 ----
1629 if (EC.isScalable()) { 0
1630 Value *NumElements = IRB.CreateElementCount(IndexTy, EC); 0
1631 ----
1632 auto [BodyIP, Index] = 0
1633 SplitBlockAndInsertSimpleForLoop(NumElements, InsertBefore); 0
1634 ----
1635 IRB.SetInsertPoint(BodyIP); 0
1636 Func(IRB, Index); 0
1637 return; 0
1638 } ----
1639 ----
1640 unsigned Num = EC.getFixedValue(); 0
1641 for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < Num; ++Idx) { 0
1642 IRB.SetInsertPoint(InsertBefore); 0
1643 Func(IRB, ConstantInt::get(IndexTy, Idx)); 0
1644 } ----
1645 } 0
1646 ----
1647 void llvm::SplitBlockAndInsertForEachLane( 0
1648 Value *EVL, Instruction *InsertBefore, ----
1649 std::function Func) { ----
1650 ----
1651 IRBuilder<> IRB(InsertBefore); 0
1652 Type *Ty = EVL->getType(); 0
1653 ----
1654 if (!isa(EVL)) { 0
1655 auto [BodyIP, Index] = SplitBlockAndInsertSimpleForLoop(EVL, InsertBefore); 0
1656 IRB.SetInsertPoint(BodyIP); 0
1657 Func(IRB, Index); 0
1658 return; 0
1659 } ----
1660 ----
1661 unsigned Num = cast(EVL)->getZExtValue(); 0
1662 for (unsigned Idx = 0; Idx < Num; ++Idx) { 0
1663 IRB.SetInsertPoint(InsertBefore); 0
1664 Func(IRB, ConstantInt::get(Ty, Idx)); 0
1665 } ----
1666 } 0
1667 ----
1668 BranchInst *llvm::GetIfCondition(BasicBlock *BB, BasicBlock *&IfTrue, 0
1669 BasicBlock *&IfFalse) { ----
1670 PHINode *SomePHI = dyn_cast(BB->begin()); 0
1671 BasicBlock *Pred1 = nullptr; 0
1672 BasicBlock *Pred2 = nullptr; 0
1673 ----
1674 if (SomePHI) { 0
1675 if (SomePHI->getNumIncomingValues() != 2) 0
1676 return nullptr; 0
1677 Pred1 = SomePHI->getIncomingBlock(0); 0
1678 Pred2 = SomePHI->getIncomingBlock(1); 0
1679 } else { ----
1680 pred_iterator PI = pred_begin(BB), PE = pred_end(BB); 0
1681 if (PI == PE) // No predecessor 0
1682 return nullptr; 0
1683 Pred1 = *PI++; 0
1684 if (PI == PE) // Only one predecessor 0
1685 return nullptr; 0
1686 Pred2 = *PI++; 0
1687 if (PI != PE) // More than two predecessors 0
1688 return nullptr; 0
1689 } ----
1690 ----
1691 // We can only handle branches. Other control flow will be lowered to ----
1692 // branches if possible anyway. ----
1693 BranchInst *Pred1Br = dyn_cast(Pred1->getTerminator()); 0
1694 BranchInst *Pred2Br = dyn_cast(Pred2->getTerminator()); 0
1695 if (!Pred1Br || !Pred2Br) 0
1696 return nullptr; 0
1697 ----
1698 // Eliminate code duplication by ensuring that Pred1Br is conditional if ----
1699 // either are. ----
1700 if (Pred2Br->isConditional()) { 0
1701 // If both branches are conditional, we don't have an "if statement". In ----
1702 // reality, we could transform this case, but since the condition will be ----
1703 // required anyway, we stand no chance of eliminating it, so the xform is ----
1704 // probably not profitable. ----
1705 if (Pred1Br->isConditional()) 0
1706 return nullptr; 0
1707 ----
1708 std::swap(Pred1, Pred2); 0
1709 std::swap(Pred1Br, Pred2Br); 0
1710 } ----
1711 ----
1712 if (Pred1Br->isConditional()) { 0
1713 // The only thing we have to watch out for here is to make sure that Pred2 ----
1714 // doesn't have incoming edges from other blocks. If it does, the condition ----
1715 // doesn't dominate BB. ----
1716 if (!Pred2->getSinglePredecessor()) 0
1717 return nullptr; 0
1718 ----
1719 // If we found a conditional branch predecessor, make sure that it branches ----
1720 // to BB and Pred2Br. If it doesn't, this isn't an "if statement". ----
1721 if (Pred1Br->getSuccessor(0) == BB && 0
1722 Pred1Br->getSuccessor(1) == Pred2) { 0
1723 IfTrue = Pred1; 0
1724 IfFalse = Pred2; 0
1725 } else if (Pred1Br->getSuccessor(0) == Pred2 && 0
1726 Pred1Br->getSuccessor(1) == BB) { 0
1727 IfTrue = Pred2; 0
1728 IfFalse = Pred1; 0
1729 } else { ----
1730 // We know that one arm of the conditional goes to BB, so the other must ----
1731 // go somewhere unrelated, and this must not be an "if statement". ----
1732 return nullptr; 0
1733 } ----
1734 ----
1735 return Pred1Br; 0
1736 } ----
1737 ----
1738 // Ok, if we got here, both predecessors end with an unconditional branch to ----
1739 // BB. Don't panic! If both blocks only have a single (identical) ----
1740 // predecessor, and THAT is a conditional branch, then we're all ok! ----
1741 BasicBlock *CommonPred = Pred1->getSinglePredecessor(); 0
1742 if (CommonPred == nullptr || CommonPred != Pred2->getSinglePredecessor()) 0
1743 return nullptr; 0
1744 ----
1745 // Otherwise, if this is a conditional branch, then we can use it! ----
1746 BranchInst *BI = dyn_cast(CommonPred->getTerminator()); 0
1747 if (!BI) return nullptr; 0
1748 ----
1749 assert(BI->isConditional() && "Two successors but not conditional?"); 0
1750 if (BI->getSuccessor(0) == Pred1) { 0
1751 IfTrue = Pred1; 0
1752 IfFalse = Pred2; 0
1753 } else { ----
1754 IfTrue = Pred2; 0
1755 IfFalse = Pred1; 0
1756 } ----
1757 return BI; 0
1758 } ----
1759 ----
1760 // After creating a control flow hub, the operands of PHINodes in an outgoing ----
1761 // block Out no longer match the predecessors of that block. Predecessors of Out ----
1762 // that are incoming blocks to the hub are now replaced by just one edge from ----
1763 // the hub. To match this new control flow, the corresponding values from each ----
1764 // PHINode must now be moved a new PHINode in the first guard block of the hub. ----
1765 // ----
1766 // This operation cannot be performed with SSAUpdater, because it involves one ----
1767 // new use: If the block Out is in the list of Incoming blocks, then the newly ----
1768 // created PHI in the Hub will use itself along that edge from Out to Hub. ----
1769 static void reconnectPhis(BasicBlock *Out, BasicBlock *GuardBlock, 0
1770 const SetVector &Incoming, ----
1771 BasicBlock *FirstGuardBlock) { ----
1772 auto I = Out->begin(); 0
1773 while (I != Out->end() && isa(I)) { 0
1774 auto Phi = cast(I); 0
1775 auto NewPhi = ----
1776 PHINode::Create(Phi->getType(), Incoming.size(), 0
1777 Phi->getName() + ".moved", &FirstGuardBlock->front()); 0
1778 for (auto *In : Incoming) { 0
1779 Value *V = UndefValue::get(Phi->getType()); 0
1780 if (In == Out) { 0
1781 V = NewPhi; 0
1782 } else if (Phi->getBasicBlockIndex(In) != -1) { 0
1783 V = Phi->removeIncomingValue(In, false); 0
1784 } ----
1785 NewPhi->addIncoming(V, In); 0
1786 } ----
1787 assert(NewPhi->getNumIncomingValues() == Incoming.size()); 0
1788 if (Phi->getNumOperands() == 0) { 0
1789 Phi->replaceAllUsesWith(NewPhi); 0
1790 I = Phi->eraseFromParent(); 0
1791 continue; 0
1792 } ----
1793 Phi->addIncoming(NewPhi, GuardBlock); 0
1794 ++I; 0
1795 } ----
1796 } 0
1797 ----
1798 using BBPredicates = DenseMap; ----
1799 using BBSetVector = SetVector; ----
1800 ----
1801 // Redirects the terminator of the incoming block to the first guard ----
1802 // block in the hub. The condition of the original terminator (if it ----
1803 // was conditional) and its original successors are returned as a ----
1804 // tuple . The function additionally filters ----
1805 // out successors that are not in the set of outgoing blocks. ----
1806 // ----
1807 // - condition is non-null iff the branch is conditional. ----
1808 // - Succ1 is non-null iff the sole/taken target is an outgoing block. ----
1809 // - Succ2 is non-null iff condition is non-null and the fallthrough ----
1810 // target is an outgoing block. ----
1811 static std::tuple ----
1812 redirectToHub(BasicBlock *BB, BasicBlock *FirstGuardBlock, 0
1813 const BBSetVector &Outgoing) { ----
1814 assert(isa(BB->getTerminator()) && 0
1815 "Only support branch terminator."); ----
1816 auto Branch = cast(BB->getTerminator()); 0
1817 auto Condition = Branch->isConditional() ? Branch->getCondition() : nullptr; 0
1818 ----
1819 BasicBlock *Succ0 = Branch->getSuccessor(0); 0
1820 BasicBlock *Succ1 = nullptr; 0
1821 Succ0 = Outgoing.count(Succ0) ? Succ0 : nullptr; 0
1822 ----
1823 if (Branch->isUnconditional()) { 0
1824 Branch->setSuccessor(0, FirstGuardBlock); 0
1825 assert(Succ0); 0
1826 } else { ----
1827 Succ1 = Branch->getSuccessor(1); 0
1828 Succ1 = Outgoing.count(Succ1) ? Succ1 : nullptr; 0
1829 assert(Succ0 || Succ1); 0
1830 if (Succ0 && !Succ1) { 0
1831 Branch->setSuccessor(0, FirstGuardBlock); 0
1832 } else if (Succ1 && !Succ0) { 0
1833 Branch->setSuccessor(1, FirstGuardBlock); 0
1834 } else { ----
1835 Branch->eraseFromParent(); 0
1836 BranchInst::Create(FirstGuardBlock, BB); 0
1837 } ----
1838 } ----
1839 ----
1840 assert(Succ0 || Succ1); 0
1841 return std::make_tuple(Condition, Succ0, Succ1); 0
1842 } ----
1843 // Setup the branch instructions for guard blocks. ----
1844 // ----
1845 // Each guard block terminates in a conditional branch that transfers ----
1846 // control to the corresponding outgoing block or the next guard ----
1847 // block. The last guard block has two outgoing blocks as successors ----
1848 // since the condition for the final outgoing block is trivially ----
1849 // true. So we create one less block (including the first guard block) ----
1850 // than the number of outgoing blocks. ----
1851 static void setupBranchForGuard(SmallVectorImpl &GuardBlocks, 0
1852 const BBSetVector &Outgoing, ----
1853 BBPredicates &GuardPredicates) { ----
1854 // To help keep the loop simple, temporarily append the last ----
1855 // outgoing block to the list of guard blocks. ----
1856 GuardBlocks.push_back(Outgoing.back()); 0
1857 ----
1858 for (int i = 0, e = GuardBlocks.size() - 1; i != e; ++i) { 0
1859 auto Out = Outgoing[i]; 0
1860 assert(GuardPredicates.count(Out)); 0
1861 BranchInst::Create(Out, GuardBlocks[i + 1], GuardPredicates[Out], 0
1862 GuardBlocks[i]); 0
1863 } ----
1864 ----
1865 // Remove the last block from the guard list. ----
1866 GuardBlocks.pop_back(); 0
1867 } 0
1868 ----
1869 /// We are using one integer to represent the block we are branching to. Then at ----
1870 /// each guard block, the predicate was calcuated using a simple `icmp eq`. ----
1871 static void calcPredicateUsingInteger( 0
1872 const BBSetVector &Incoming, const BBSetVector &Outgoing, ----
1873 SmallVectorImpl &GuardBlocks, BBPredicates &GuardPredicates) { ----
1874 auto &Context = Incoming.front()->getContext(); 0
1875 auto FirstGuardBlock = GuardBlocks.front(); 0
1876 ----
1877 auto Phi = PHINode::Create(Type::getInt32Ty(Context), Incoming.size(), 0
1878 "merged.bb.idx", FirstGuardBlock); ----
1879 ----
1880 for (auto In : Incoming) { 0
1881 Value *Condition; ----
1882 BasicBlock *Succ0; ----
1883 BasicBlock *Succ1; ----
1884 std::tie(Condition, Succ0, Succ1) = 0
1885 redirectToHub(In, FirstGuardBlock, Outgoing); 0
1886 Value *IncomingId = nullptr; 0
1887 if (Succ0 && Succ1) { 0
1888 // target_bb_index = Condition ? index_of_succ0 : index_of_succ1. ----
1889 auto Succ0Iter = find(Outgoing, Succ0); 0
1890 auto Succ1Iter = find(Outgoing, Succ1); 0
1891 Value *Id0 = ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt32Ty(Context), 0
1892 std::distance(Outgoing.begin(), Succ0Iter)); 0
1893 Value *Id1 = ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt32Ty(Context), 0
1894 std::distance(Outgoing.begin(), Succ1Iter)); 0
1895 IncomingId = SelectInst::Create(Condition, Id0, Id1, "target.bb.idx", 0
1896 In->getTerminator()); ----
1897 } else { 0
1898 // Get the index of the non-null successor. ----
1899 auto SuccIter = Succ0 ? find(Outgoing, Succ0) : find(Outgoing, Succ1); 0
1900 IncomingId = ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt32Ty(Context), 0
1901 std::distance(Outgoing.begin(), SuccIter)); 0
1902 } ----
1903 Phi->addIncoming(IncomingId, In); 0
1904 } ----
1905 ----
1906 for (int i = 0, e = Outgoing.size() - 1; i != e; ++i) { 0
1907 auto Out = Outgoing[i]; 0
1908 auto Cmp = ICmpInst::Create(Instruction::ICmp, ICmpInst::ICMP_EQ, Phi, 0
1909 ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt32Ty(Context), i), 0
1910 Out->getName() + ".predicate", GuardBlocks[i]); 0
1911 GuardPredicates[Out] = Cmp; 0
1912 } ----
1913 } 0
1914 ----
1915 /// We record the predicate of each outgoing block using a phi of boolean. ----
1916 static void calcPredicateUsingBooleans( 0
1917 const BBSetVector &Incoming, const BBSetVector &Outgoing, ----
1918 SmallVectorImpl &GuardBlocks, BBPredicates &GuardPredicates, ----
1919 SmallVectorImpl &DeletionCandidates) { ----
1920 auto &Context = Incoming.front()->getContext(); 0
1921 auto BoolTrue = ConstantInt::getTrue(Context); 0
1922 auto BoolFalse = ConstantInt::getFalse(Context); 0
1923 auto FirstGuardBlock = GuardBlocks.front(); 0
1924 ----
1925 // The predicate for the last outgoing is trivially true, and so we ----
1926 // process only the first N-1 successors. ----
1927 for (int i = 0, e = Outgoing.size() - 1; i != e; ++i) { 0
1928 auto Out = Outgoing[i]; 0
1929 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Creating guard for " << Out->getName() << "\n"); 0
1930 ----
1931 auto Phi = ----
1932 PHINode::Create(Type::getInt1Ty(Context), Incoming.size(), 0
1933 StringRef("Guard.") + Out->getName(), FirstGuardBlock); 0
1934 GuardPredicates[Out] = Phi; 0
1935 } ----
1936 ----
1937 for (auto *In : Incoming) { 0
1938 Value *Condition; ----
1939 BasicBlock *Succ0; ----
1940 BasicBlock *Succ1; ----
1941 std::tie(Condition, Succ0, Succ1) = 0
1942 redirectToHub(In, FirstGuardBlock, Outgoing); 0
1943 ----
1944 // Optimization: Consider an incoming block A with both successors ----
1945 // Succ0 and Succ1 in the set of outgoing blocks. The predicates ----
1946 // for Succ0 and Succ1 complement each other. If Succ0 is visited ----
1947 // first in the loop below, control will branch to Succ0 using the ----
1948 // corresponding predicate. But if that branch is not taken, then ----
1949 // control must reach Succ1, which means that the incoming value of ----
1950 // the predicate from `In` is true for Succ1. ----
1951 bool OneSuccessorDone = false; 0
1952 for (int i = 0, e = Outgoing.size() - 1; i != e; ++i) { 0
1953 auto Out = Outgoing[i]; 0
1954 PHINode *Phi = cast(GuardPredicates[Out]); 0
1955 if (Out != Succ0 && Out != Succ1) { 0
1956 Phi->addIncoming(BoolFalse, In); 0
1957 } else if (!Succ0 || !Succ1 || OneSuccessorDone) { 0
1958 // Optimization: When only one successor is an outgoing block, ----
1959 // the incoming predicate from `In` is always true. ----
1960 Phi->addIncoming(BoolTrue, In); 0
1961 } else { ----
1962 assert(Succ0 && Succ1); 0
1963 if (Out == Succ0) { 0
1964 Phi->addIncoming(Condition, In); 0
1965 } else { ----
1966 auto Inverted = invertCondition(Condition); 0
1967 DeletionCandidates.push_back(Condition); 0
1968 Phi->addIncoming(Inverted, In); 0
1969 } ----
1970 OneSuccessorDone = true; 0
1971 } ----
1972 } ----
1973 } ----
1974 } 0
1975 ----
1976 // Capture the existing control flow as guard predicates, and redirect ----
1977 // control flow from \p Incoming block through the \p GuardBlocks to the ----
1978 // \p Outgoing blocks. ----
1979 // ----
1980 // There is one guard predicate for each outgoing block OutBB. The ----
1981 // predicate represents whether the hub should transfer control flow ----
1982 // to OutBB. These predicates are NOT ORTHOGONAL. The Hub evaluates ----
1983 // them in the same order as the Outgoing set-vector, and control ----
1984 // branches to the first outgoing block whose predicate evaluates to true. ----
1985 static void ----
1986 convertToGuardPredicates(SmallVectorImpl &GuardBlocks, 0
1987 SmallVectorImpl &DeletionCandidates, ----
1988 const BBSetVector &Incoming, ----
1989 const BBSetVector &Outgoing, const StringRef Prefix, ----
1990 std::optional MaxControlFlowBooleans) { ----
1991 BBPredicates GuardPredicates; 0
1992 auto F = Incoming.front()->getParent(); 0
1993 ----
1994 for (int i = 0, e = Outgoing.size() - 1; i != e; ++i) 0
1995 GuardBlocks.push_back( 0
1996 BasicBlock::Create(F->getContext(), Prefix + ".guard", F)); 0
1997 ----
1998 // When we are using an integer to record which target block to jump to, we ----
1999 // are creating less live values, actually we are using one single integer to ----
2000 // store the index of the target block. When we are using booleans to store ----
2001 // the branching information, we need (N-1) boolean values, where N is the ----
2002 // number of outgoing block. ----
2003 if (!MaxControlFlowBooleans || Outgoing.size() <= *MaxControlFlowBooleans) 0
2004 calcPredicateUsingBooleans(Incoming, Outgoing, GuardBlocks, GuardPredicates, 0
2005 DeletionCandidates); ----
2006 else ----
2007 calcPredicateUsingInteger(Incoming, Outgoing, GuardBlocks, GuardPredicates); 0
2008 ----
2009 setupBranchForGuard(GuardBlocks, Outgoing, GuardPredicates); 0
2010 } 0
2011 ----
2012 BasicBlock *llvm::CreateControlFlowHub( 0
2013 DomTreeUpdater *DTU, SmallVectorImpl &GuardBlocks, ----
2014 const BBSetVector &Incoming, const BBSetVector &Outgoing, ----
2015 const StringRef Prefix, std::optional MaxControlFlowBooleans) { ----
2016 if (Outgoing.size() < 2) 0
2017 return Outgoing.front(); 0
2018 ----
2019 SmallVector Updates; 0
2020 if (DTU) { 0
2021 for (auto *In : Incoming) { 0
2022 for (auto Succ : successors(In)) 0
2023 if (Outgoing.count(Succ)) 0
2024 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Delete, In, Succ}); 0
2025 } ----
2026 } ----
2027 ----
2028 SmallVector DeletionCandidates; 0
2029 convertToGuardPredicates(GuardBlocks, DeletionCandidates, Incoming, Outgoing, 0
2030 Prefix, MaxControlFlowBooleans); ----
2031 auto FirstGuardBlock = GuardBlocks.front(); 0
2032 ----
2033 // Update the PHINodes in each outgoing block to match the new control flow. ----
2034 for (int i = 0, e = GuardBlocks.size(); i != e; ++i) 0
2035 reconnectPhis(Outgoing[i], GuardBlocks[i], Incoming, FirstGuardBlock); 0
2036 ----
2037 reconnectPhis(Outgoing.back(), GuardBlocks.back(), Incoming, FirstGuardBlock); 0
2038 ----
2039 if (DTU) { 0
2040 int NumGuards = GuardBlocks.size(); 0
2041 assert((int)Outgoing.size() == NumGuards + 1); 0
2042 ----
2043 for (auto In : Incoming) 0
2044 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Insert, In, FirstGuardBlock}); 0
2045 ----
2046 for (int i = 0; i != NumGuards - 1; ++i) { 0
2047 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Insert, GuardBlocks[i], Outgoing[i]}); 0
2048 Updates.push_back( 0
2049 {DominatorTree::Insert, GuardBlocks[i], GuardBlocks[i + 1]}); 0
2050 } ----
2051 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Insert, GuardBlocks[NumGuards - 1], 0
2052 Outgoing[NumGuards - 1]}); 0
2053 Updates.push_back({DominatorTree::Insert, GuardBlocks[NumGuards - 1], 0
2054 Outgoing[NumGuards]}); 0
2055 DTU->applyUpdates(Updates); 0
2056 } ----
2057 ----
2058 for (auto I : DeletionCandidates) { 0
2059 if (I->use_empty()) 0
2060 if (auto Inst = dyn_cast_or_null(I)) 0
2061 Inst->eraseFromParent(); 0
2062 } 0
2063 ----
2064 return FirstGuardBlock; 0
2065 } 0
2066 ----
2067 void llvm::InvertBranch(BranchInst *PBI, IRBuilderBase &Builder) { 0
2068 Value *NewCond = PBI->getCondition(); 0
2069 // If this is a "cmp" instruction, only used for branching (and nowhere ----
2070 // else), then we can simply invert the predicate. ----
2071 if (NewCond->hasOneUse() && isa(NewCond)) { 0
2072 CmpInst *CI = cast(NewCond); 0
2073 CI->setPredicate(CI->getInversePredicate()); 0
2074 } else ----
2075 NewCond = Builder.CreateNot(NewCond, NewCond->getName() + ".not"); 0
2076 ----
2077 PBI->setCondition(NewCond); 0
2078 PBI->swapSuccessors(); 0
2079 } 0
